          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p> In 1995, Professor Konstantin Korotkov built the first Gas Discharge Visualization device by hand in Saint Petersburg. That single prototype launched a new field of biophysics — and eventually became Bio-Well. Today, his technology is used by researchers, practitioners, and institutions across more than 70 countries, backed by peer-reviewed science and over 30 defended doctoral dissertations.</p>",
